<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,159,327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,200,159,183]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authority="Sw." authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1788" box="[234,497,159,183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Melastoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornatum">
<emphasis box="[234,451,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Melastoma ornatum</emphasis>
Sw.
</taxonomicName>
is the oldest basionym for this species and it was omitted from the list of synonyms by 
<bibRefCitation author="Guimaraes, P. J. F. &amp; Michelangeli F. A. &amp; Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R." box="[136,398,195,219]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="937 - 1002" refId="ref2118" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F., Michelangeli F. A., Sosa, K. &amp; Santiago, J. R. (2019) Systematics of Tibouchina and allies (Melastomataceae: Melastomateae): a new taxonomic classification. Taxon 68: 937 - 1002. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12151" type="journal article" year="2019">
Guimarães 
<emphasis box="[260,315,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
. Because the combination 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vahl) P. J. F. Guim. &amp; Michelang." authorityName="P. J. F. Guim. &amp; Michelang." baseAuthorityName="Vahl" box="[689,1322,195,219]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Chaetogastra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inconstans">
<emphasis box="[689,957,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Chaetogastra inconstans</emphasis>
(Vahl) P.J.F.Guim. &amp; Michelang.
</taxonomicName>
is based on a more recent synonym (
<taxonomicName authority="Vahl (1797: 37)" authorityName="Vahl" authorityPageNumber="37" authorityYear="1797" box="[406,782,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inconstans">
<emphasis box="[406,602,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Rhexia inconstans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vahl, M." box="[611,782,231,255]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" refId="ref2621" refString="Vahl, M. (1797) Eclogae americanae, seu, Descriptiones plantarum praesertim Americae meridionalis, nondum cognitarum. Vol. 1. Havniae [Copenhagen]: Impensis Auctoris, 52 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 429" type="book" year="1797">Vahl (1797: 37)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a new combination for the basionym with priority is needed. 
